<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-07-14T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-07-14T05:00:00-05:00" n="611" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d611">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5034 Registration/4: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-14T18:00:00+08:00">July 14, 1930—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 14—10:05 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>573. Shanghai’s July 12, 11 a.m. and previous. Does the Department feel
                            in a position to make a ruling on the basis of Shanghai’s telegrams
                            referred to above or does it desire to await receipt of radio summary of
                            regulations mentioned in penultimate paragraph of Shanghai’s July 12, 11
                            a.m.?</p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>